  "descriptions": {
    "nginx": "nginx-thrift front-end. Given a CPU station (cpuCores 3 x 1000 / cpuTimePerRequestMs 1 ms => ~3,000 req/s) so the CPU-bound front-end becomes the LOW-load bottleneck the DeathStarBench paper reports (ASPLOS 2019: 'bottleneck shifts front-end nginx at low load -> back-end databases at high load'). The CPU time equals its 1 ms proxy latency, so the low-load per-hop sojourn (hence MongoDB's measured latency share) is unchanged; only the ceiling moves. The core count is an ESTIMATE (no absolute front-end req/s is published) chosen to sit just below the post-storage MongoDB tier's ceiling."
  },
